What does root.get("age"), age mean in cb.greaterThan(root.get("age"), age)?

(i) root.get("age"):
This does not return the value of the age field for a specific user.
Instead, it returns a reference to the "age" field/column in the database table for use in
building a query.

(ii) age (the second parameter):
This is the actual value you want to compare against (for example, 18).

How does it work?
When you write:

cb.greaterThan(root.get("age"), age)

You are telling JPA:
"Build a condition where the value in the age column of the table is greater than the value
of the age parameter I provided."

In SQL terms, it’s like:

WHERE age > 18

The first age is the column in the table (root.get("age")).
The second age is the value you’re comparing to (the method parameter).

In Short:
root.get("age"): Refers to the column in the database.
age: Refers to the value you want to compare against.

You need both:
One to tell JPA which column to use,
One to tell it what value to compare to.